      "inheritance_hierarchy": "Core contracts inherit EssentialContract (UUPSUpgradeable + Ownable2StepUpgradeable + AddressResolver). TaikoL1 extends EssentialContract and composes protocol logic via libraries LibProposing/LibProving/LibVerifying/LibDepositing/LibUtils. AssignmentHook is an EssentialContract implementing IHook and is called by TaikoL1 during proposeBlock. Guardians is an abstract EssentialContract used by GuardianProver; GuardianProver calls TaikoL1.proveBlock once enough guardian approvals collected. Tier providers (Mainnet/Testnet/DevnetTierProvider) are EssentialContract implementations of ITierProvider (pure getters). Verifiers: SgxVerifier and GuardianVerifier are EssentialContract implementations of IVerifier and are invoked by TaikoL1 via LibProving, resolved by tier.verifierName through AddressResolver. Governance: TaikoGovernor is EssentialContract + OZ Governor modules; TaikoTimelockController is EssentialContract + OZ TimelockControllerUpgradeable. TaikoToken is EssentialContract + OZ ERC20SnapshotVotes stack. AddressManager is EssentialContract and stores chainId/name->address mapping.",
      "external_dependencies": [
        "OpenZeppelin upgradeable: UUPSUpgradeable, Ownable2StepUpgradeable, GovernorUpgradeable, GovernorCompatibilityBravoUpgradeable, GovernorVotesUpgradeable, GovernorVotesQuorumFractionUpgradeable, GovernorTimelockControlUpgradeable, TimelockControllerUpgradeable, ERC20Upgradeable, ERC20SnapshotUpgradeable, ERC20VotesUpgradeable",
        "OpenZeppelin non-upgradeable: IERC20, SafeERC20, Address, ECDSA, IERC165, IERC1271",
        "EIP-4844 blobhash opcode usage and KZG point evaluation precompile (Lib4844 address(0x0A))",
        "Automata DCAP attestation interface IAttestation + V3 quote structs",
        "Nomad ExcessivelySafeCall",
        "External protocol contracts via resolver: bridge, signal_service, tier_provider, taiko_token, verifier facets (tier_sgx, tier_sgx_zkvm, tier_guardian, tier_optimistic), guardian_prover, proposer/proposer_one, chain_pauser, rollup_watchdog, snapshooter, automata_dcap_attestation"
      ],
      "upgrade_patterns": "UUPS (ERC1967) upgradeability via EssentialContract inheriting UUPSUpgradeable; upgrades authorized by onlyOwner. All EssentialContract children expose UUPSUpgradeable external upgrade entrypoints unless removed; libraries are stateless. No Diamond/Beacon/Transparent proxies shown in code snippet but contracts are designed to be deployed behind ERC1967 proxies.",
      "access_control_structure": "Owner-centric access control (Ownable2StepUpgradeable) with additional named-role resolution via AddressResolver: onlyFromOwnerOrNamed(name) used for selective permissions (e.g., TaikoL1 pause by owner or chain_pauser; AssignmentHook callable only by resolved 'taiko'; TaikoToken snapshot by owner or snapshooter; SgxVerifier delete by owner or rollup_watchdog). Guardians adds an on-chain guardian set with bitmap approvals; onlyOwner manages guardian set; only guardians can approve operations. Timelock has OZ role-based control; custom getMinDelay grants TIMELOCK_ADMIN_ROLE callers a 0 delay."
    },
